content.description: Climb large crack on south face of boulder.  The right side of the crack is actually a large detached block(little loose).  Reach into the crack and you can lay-back off the block.
content.location: South face of boulder.  Just around the corner of Loompa Land.

content.description: Start matched on a good low sidepull and do some tensiony moves up a series of sidepulls.
content.location: In the trees along the right side of the Anchorpoint talus field.  Just downhill from the Duke/Dutchess boulder.

content.description: Start on a good left hand sidepull and a crimp for the right and climb some fun, engaging moves up a cool face.
content.location: In the trees along the right edge of the Anchorpoint Talus Field.

content.description: Start left hand on a pinch and right on a good undercling.  Go up and left through a sharp crimp.
content.location: In the trees along the right side of the Anchorpoint talus field.

content.description: Start the same as the Dutchess but move up and right around the arete on cool holds.
content.location: In the trees along the right edge of the Anchorpoint talus field.

content.description: Climb up boulder using three options(All V0).  Climb up using both cracks;  Climb up just center crack; or climb up left side with crack and arete.
content.location: Just north of the Loompa Land boulder by 20ft.  Take the trail till you reach the woods that divide that Anchor-point boulders and the 500ft proper.  Head straight up hill and you will run right into this.

content.description: Starts on a sharp left hand crimp and a good right hand undercling.  Move through sloping lip holds to the topout.
content.protection: Several pads, a hole like landing, still a bit heads up but doable.
content.location: On the opposite side of the boulder as Empty Space.

content.description: In the trees, between boulder fields, you will find a few free standing boulders with some fun stuff. Â Empty Space is pretty darn good and the rest are definitely worth checking out.. They are right there after all.
